com.ge.predix.solsvc.ext.util

Class JsonMapper

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ge.predix.solsvc.ext.util.JsonMapper
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IJsonMapper

    @Component
public final class JsonMapper
extends Object
implements IJsonMapper
    This class helps implement Polymorphic (Animal, Cat, Dog) marshaling and unmarshaling. use @JsonTypeInfo annotation on the Parent class to be marshaled or unmarshaled, then add it here When using maps or lists as a property, use @JsonSerialize and @JsonDeserialize annotations on the property to be unmarshaled or marshaled, the keys or values that are polymorphic will be serialized or deserialized if they inherit a parent class registered here
    Author:

      • fromJsonArray

        public <P> List<P> fromJsonArray(String json,
                                 String clazz)
        You have a json array, you know the Parent (P), you know the spelling of the child class, but you don't have a handle to the child java Class. Since we registered all the child class upon startup, it looks through the registered child classes until it finds a name match. e.g. Say you have an Engine P. And you have a physical GE90Engine extends Engine. This happens when processing many different types of Assets from PredixAsset through the same code.
